    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> and your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably with a matching lid), with a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> and<strong> garlic</strong> and cook for 7-8 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-leek-potato-and-mustard-pie-with-asparagus/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel your <strong>potatoes</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>peeled potatoes</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and chop into large chunks</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-leek-potato-and-mustard-pie-with-asparagus/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> and <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> finely</p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the<strong> chopped potatoes </strong>and <strong>leek</strong> to the pan with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper </strong>and mix everything together</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-leek-potato-and-mustard-pie-with-asparagus/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[350ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [450ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> with your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>grated cheddar</strong>, 1/3<strong> </strong>of your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and mix it all together and cook for 6-7 min \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy leek & potato mixture</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-leek-potato-and-mustard-pie-with-asparagus/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap your <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>pastry</strong> into triangles, roughly the size of your palm</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-leek-potato-and-mustard-pie-with-asparagus/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>cheesy leek & potato mixture</strong> to an<strong> oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Top the mixture with the <strong>pastry triangles</strong>, leaving some gaps in between and brush with a little <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and put the dish in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and bubbling \u2013 this is your <strong>cheesy leek, potato & mustard pie</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-leek-potato-and-mustard-pie-with-asparagus/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>asparagus</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>(or two!) with a large splash of <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the<strong> asparagus</strong> to form a tightly sealed parcel and add to a baking tray</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Make 2 separate parcels!</p><p>When the pie is almost ready, put the tray in the oven for 8-10 min or until the asparagus are tender with a slight bite</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-leek-potato-and-mustard-pie-with-asparagus/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cheesy leek, potato & mustard pie </strong>with the <strong>steamed asparagus </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
